article.headline: Jimerson leads Saint Louis past Saint Joseph's 88-85
article.description: — Gibson Jimerson scored 24 of his 27 points in the second half and Saint Louis rallied past Saint Joseph's (Pa.) 88-85 on Wednesday night.
article.linkText: Jimerson leads Saint Louis past Saint Joseph's 88-85
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- — Gibson Jimerson scored 24 of his 27 points in the second half and Saint Louis rallied past Saint Joseph's (Pa.) 88-85 on Wednesday night. Jimerson was 8 of 14 shooting, including 7 for 11 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line for the Billikens (8-8, 1-2 Atlantic 10 Conference). Tim Dalger scored 15 points while going 5 of 7 and 3 of 4 from the free throw line. Bradley Ezewiro was 3 of 8 shooting and 6 of 7 from the free throw line to finish with 12 points, while adding six rebounds. Erik Reynolds II finished with 27 points for the Hawks (10-5, 0-2). Lynn Greer III added 18 points, seven rebounds and five assists for Saint Joseph's. Christ Essandoko also recorded 12 points and eight rebounds. Saint Louis went into halftime trailing 43-33. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
